*openssh-5.9_p1-r13 (02 Jan 2014)

  02 Jan 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openssh-5.9_p1-r13.ebuild, -openssh-5.9_p1-r12.ebuild:
  Err, actually, don't run ssh-update-known-hosts in postinst,
  this results in an empty known_hosts since UPDATE does
  not see /etc/jails.

*openssh-5.9_p1-r12 (02 Jan 2014)

  02 Jan 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openssh-5.9_p1-r12.ebuild, -openssh-5.9_p1-r11.ebuild:
  Install ssh_config.rm, not ssh_conf (hardcoded crypto), in
  RM client packages.

*openssh-5.9_p1-r11 (02 Jan 2014)

  02 Jan 2014; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openssh-5.9_p1-r11.ebuild, -openssh-5.9_p1-r10.ebuild,
  +files/ssh-update-known-hosts:
  Add a script to update /mounts/user_root/etc/known_hosts
  based on the contents of /etc/jails/*/ssh. Call it after
  generating host keys in postinst for packages built with
  USE server.

*openssh-5.9_p1-r10 (24 Dec 2013)

  24 Dec 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +openssh-5.9_p1-r10.ebuild, -openssh-5.9_p1-r9.ebuild,
  files/clip/sshd_config.admin, files/clip/sshd_config.audit:
  Change ebuild to be used separately for client and server 
  configurations, so that we can now build for CLIP : 
   - openssh (client only)
   - openssh-admin (admin server only), with DEB_NAME_SUFFIX
     and CLIP_VROOTS chosen accordingly
   - openssh-audit (audit server only)
  The main advantage is that we can now build other openssh-<>
  servers for other jails which might need remote access.

*openssh-5.9_p1-r9 (28 May 2013)

  28 May 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
