  28 Jul 2006; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  openssh-4.3_p2-r1.ebuild:
  OK, having both clip-ssh and clip-sshd as USE flags is broken,
  since we would need to install the package twice in the update
  view. Modified so that clip-ssh does not remove sshd, but simply
  moves it to /admin_root/sbin (regardless of CPREFIX). Thus we 
  only need that package in the update view.
  Note: left clip-sshd USE flag as is, for now.
  TODO : explode config files beetween /usr/local/etc and 
  admin_root/something ? Is this at all feasible ?

